1
00:01:04,952 --> 00:01:06,271
Hey.

2
00:01:07,072 --> 00:01:08,949
Hey, you, whoever you are.

3
00:01:09,112 --> 00:01:11,785
- Are you awake now, princess?
- I want a drink.

4
00:01:12,192 --> 00:01:15,104
- Oh, soon, princess.
- I want it now.

5
00:01:16,272 --> 00:01:18,149
Oh, please...

6
00:01:18,312 --> 00:01:20,667
...please get me a drink.

7
00:01:20,832 --> 00:01:23,300
For Gods sake, baby,
don't hold out on me.

8
00:01:23,472 --> 00:01:24,746
Is coming up, princess.

9
00:02:22,112 --> 00:02:23,545
Princess.

10
00:04:06,272 --> 00:04:09,150
Those two flags just
ought about do it, boys.

11
00:04:10,192 --> 00:04:13,980
Well, don't tell me that man with the
middle-age spread is Dan Hatcher.

12
00:04:15,632 --> 00:04:18,226
Chance. Chance Wayne.

13
00:04:19,752 --> 00:04:22,391
I never expected to see you again.
Not in these hereabouts.

14
00:04:22,552 --> 00:04:24,588
Just because a man's
successful is no reason...

15
00:04:24,752 --> 00:04:28,222
...to forget his old hometown.
- Anything I can do for you, Mr. Wayne?

16
00:04:30,592 --> 00:04:31,866
Yeah, I want a suite.

17
00:04:32,032 --> 00:04:33,590
Facing outside to the gulf.

18
00:04:33,752 --> 00:04:35,504
Bedroom, living room, the best.

19
00:04:35,672 --> 00:04:38,789
And also service that car out there.

20
00:04:39,552 --> 00:04:41,941
The Cadillac convertible out front.

21
00:04:43,512 --> 00:04:45,343
"Princess Kosmos."

22
00:04:46,112 --> 00:04:47,625
"Princess Kos" what?

23
00:04:47,792 --> 00:04:50,704
Kosmonopolis.
The Princess Kosmonopolis.

24
00:04:51,352 --> 00:04:53,388
Hollywood, California?

25
00:04:53,912 --> 00:04:55,868
She is traveling incognito.

26
00:04:56,032 --> 00:04:58,262
Can I let you in on a little secret?

27
00:04:59,672 --> 00:05:04,268
She is also Alexandra Del Lago,
the movie star.

28
00:05:05,672 --> 00:05:09,790
She's not feeling very well. Car sickness.
I'll take her up by the veranda.

29
00:05:09,952 --> 00:05:11,385
Honey...

30
00:05:11,552 --> 00:05:13,782
...get me Dr. Scudder
at the Finley Hospital.

31
00:05:15,792 --> 00:05:17,020
Hey.

32
00:05:29,112 --> 00:05:32,343
Oh, is chance Wayne, all right, sir.
Big as life.

33
00:05:32,672 --> 00:05:35,061
No, doc, he's not exactly alone.

34
00:05:36,192 --> 00:05:38,865
Princess Kosmo
or something or another.

35
00:05:39,032 --> 00:05:41,148
He said she's a moving-picture star.

36
00:05:53,312 --> 00:05:55,746
Will you be right over? How soon?

37
00:06:09,712 --> 00:06:13,546
Honey, try to get me Boss Finley
on the phone, will you, please?

38
00:06:14,352 --> 00:06:16,661
Did you ever hear of
Princess Kosta-whatsit or...?

39
00:06:28,672 --> 00:06:30,151
Hey.

40
00:06:31,032 --> 00:06:34,263
- What are you doing?
- Don't you want these unpacked, sir?

41
00:06:35,272 --> 00:06:37,149
The princess is finicky
about her things.

42
00:06:37,312 --> 00:06:38,904
I'll take care of that later.

43
00:06:39,072 --> 00:06:40,505
Yes, sir.

44
00:06:40,872 --> 00:06:43,147
And about that bottle...

45
00:06:43,312 --> 00:06:44,825
I didn't see any bottle, Mr. Wayne.

46
00:06:45,712 --> 00:06:48,101
- How'd you know my name?
- I used to wait tables...

47
00:06:48,272 --> 00:06:51,344
<i>...at the club when you'd come
dancing with the same young lady.</i>

48
00:06:51,512 --> 00:06:54,504
That pretty young lady.
Boss Finley's daughter.

49
00:06:55,112 --> 00:06:56,511
Yeah.

50
00:06:57,912 --> 00:06:59,903
- What are you called?
- Fly.

51
00:07:00,072 --> 00:07:01,471
Just like the fly, sir.

52
00:07:02,632 --> 00:07:03,951
Fly.

53
00:07:04,392 --> 00:07:06,303
And when you haul up the rest,
would you...

54
00:07:06,472 --> 00:07:08,542
...bring up a bottle of vodka
and some ice?

55
00:07:08,712 --> 00:07:09,906
Yes, sir.

56
00:07:10,072 --> 00:07:13,189
And write yourself
a $5 tip on the check.

57
00:07:13,352 --> 00:07:14,705
Yes, sir.

58
00:07:15,312 --> 00:07:16,984
Now, shoo, Fly.

59
00:08:14,672 --> 00:08:17,061
Is okay, princess. Is okay.

60
00:08:30,472 --> 00:08:32,383
Good evening, doctor.

61
00:08:44,832 --> 00:08:47,221
- Who's that?
- George Scudder.

62
00:08:54,592 --> 00:08:56,469
Hello, doc.
How'd you know I was back?

63
00:08:56,632 --> 00:08:59,146
Bad news travels fast.

64
00:08:59,472 --> 00:09:02,828
Is very nice of you to make my
homecoming so warm and so friendly.

65
00:09:02,992 --> 00:09:05,506
Your lady friend sounds like
she's coming out of ether.

66
00:09:05,672 --> 00:09:07,628
The princess had a rough night.
Traveling.

67
00:09:07,792 --> 00:09:10,909
- You hooked a princess? Gee!
- She's not using her real name...

68
00:09:11,072 --> 00:09:13,791
Golly, I should think not,
checking into hotels with you.

69
00:09:13,952 --> 00:09:15,988
George. You are the only
grown man I know...

70
00:09:16,152 --> 00:09:18,382
<i>...that still says "gee"
and "golly" and "gosh."</i>

71
00:09:18,552 --> 00:09:20,986
Well, I'm not as sophisticated as you.

72
00:09:21,152 --> 00:09:23,541
Get me the Thomas J. Finley Hospital,
please.

73
00:09:24,952 --> 00:09:28,342
- How's Heavenly?
- Don't tell me she's why you came back.

74
00:09:28,512 --> 00:09:31,106
Hello, this is Dr. Scudder. Any calls?

75
00:09:33,632 --> 00:09:36,226
<i>Well, you tell her the
cesarean scar won't be visible...</i>

76
00:09:36,392 --> 00:09:37,950
...to anyone except her husband.

77
00:09:38,112 --> 00:09:39,511
At least, I hope not.

78
00:09:39,672 --> 00:09:43,585
All right. I'll take care of that.
I'll be there in 20 minutes. Right.

79
00:09:43,752 --> 00:09:45,902
You sure got the
bedside manner, George.

80
00:09:46,072 --> 00:09:49,951
Well, I don't get much practice
since I was made chief of staff.

81
00:09:50,112 --> 00:09:52,672
Oh, man. You've got it made.

82
00:09:52,832 --> 00:09:54,504
Why did you come back here?

83
00:09:54,672 --> 00:09:57,630
Well, I still got a mother
and a girl here, thas why.

84
00:09:59,632 --> 00:10:01,987
Mother's been waiting
for the surprise that I got.

85
00:10:02,152 --> 00:10:06,623
But you asked "How's Heavenly,"
not "How's my mother."

86
00:10:15,072 --> 00:10:17,381
I'll take that. The luggage
in the bedroom, please.

87
00:10:17,552 --> 00:10:18,951
Yes, sir.

88
00:10:27,312 --> 00:10:28,631
Does a...

89
00:10:28,792 --> 00:10:31,226
...chief of staff take a snort, George?

90
00:10:31,392 --> 00:10:32,825
Your...

91
00:10:33,312 --> 00:10:35,906
Your mother died a few weeks ago.

92
00:10:47,912 --> 00:10:50,142
This is the death certificate.

93
00:10:52,512 --> 00:10:54,309
Why wasn't I notified?

94
00:10:54,472 --> 00:10:55,700
Well, you were.

95
00:10:55,872 --> 00:10:58,432
A few days before she died,
I sent you a telegram.

96
00:10:58,592 --> 00:11:00,787
The last address she had for you.

97
00:11:00,952 --> 00:11:03,705
General delivery, Hollywood.

98
00:11:03,872 --> 00:11:05,191
I got no telegram.

99
00:11:05,352 --> 00:11:09,664
After she died, I sent you a letter.
And we never heard from you.

100
00:11:09,832 --> 00:11:11,629
The church took up a nice collection...

101
00:11:11,792 --> 00:11:14,431
...and she was nicely buried
in the family plot.

102
00:11:18,912 --> 00:11:21,506
Don't you even care
that your mother died?

103
00:11:29,072 --> 00:11:30,983
What is that you just took?

104
00:11:31,152 --> 00:11:32,824
A pill.

105
00:11:33,392 --> 00:11:34,666
What kind of pill?

106
00:11:34,832 --> 00:11:37,187
Oh, benny. Benzedrine.

107
00:11:37,352 --> 00:11:39,388
On prescription?

108
00:11:40,432 --> 00:11:42,866
Yeah. Sort of.

109
00:11:43,032 --> 00:11:45,910
A goofball makes the world
keep its balance.

110
00:11:46,072 --> 00:11:49,508
- I don't understand you. I just don't...
- I don't expect you to, George.

111
00:11:49,672 --> 00:11:51,902
I mean your coming back here,
after what I wrote.

112
00:11:52,072 --> 00:11:55,064
- You'll be late, chief.
- I wrote you not to come back here ever.

113
00:11:55,232 --> 00:11:57,029
I wrote how Finley
and Tom Jr. Feel...

114
00:11:57,192 --> 00:11:59,865
...about your recent behavior
toward a certain young lady.

115
00:12:00,032 --> 00:12:02,466
- And I also wrote you how that...
- Look, I told you.

116
00:12:02,632 --> 00:12:06,511
Now, I got no letter, I got no telegram.
You got something to tell me, tell me.

117
00:12:06,672 --> 00:12:09,140
I got no letter about
any certain young...

118
00:12:13,592 --> 00:12:15,867
Something happen to Heavenly, George?
Is that it?

119
00:12:16,032 --> 00:12:19,707
Something about Heavenly?
What else did you write in that letter?

120
00:12:19,872 --> 00:12:23,911
Well, I see we can't possibly
discuss this in a civilized manner.

121
00:12:28,272 --> 00:12:29,591
All right.

122
00:12:31,112 --> 00:12:33,831
George, if something happened
to Heavenly, tell me, please.

123
00:12:33,992 --> 00:12:35,710
- Give me that bag.
- First tell me.

124
00:12:35,872 --> 00:12:37,544
First the bag.

125
00:12:41,192 --> 00:12:43,626
Now, I'm gonna give you
the best advice you ever had.

126
00:12:43,792 --> 00:12:46,625
Take that advice. Get out of town.

127
00:12:46,792 --> 00:12:48,862
You know what the name
Boss Finley means...

128
00:12:49,032 --> 00:12:52,229
<i>...so don't try to see
Heavenly or talk to her or anything.</i>

129
00:12:53,472 --> 00:12:54,666
Now...

130
00:12:54,832 --> 00:12:57,107
<i>...I'll tell the clerk you're checking out.</i>

131
00:12:57,272 --> 00:13:00,184
Go wake Sleeping Beauty
out of her drunken jag and get moving.

132
00:13:00,352 --> 00:13:03,264
And keep moving till
you're across the state line.

133
00:13:06,912 --> 00:13:08,868
I ain't moving nowhere
till I see my girl.

134
00:13:09,032 --> 00:13:11,182
You don't have a girl in St. Cloud.

135
00:13:11,352 --> 00:13:15,425
Thas what else I wrote. Heavenly
and I are getting married next month.

136
00:13:17,032 --> 00:13:18,784
Excuse me.

137
00:13:23,592 --> 00:13:25,469
You drive carefully, now.

138
00:13:39,952 --> 00:13:41,943
Operator? Give me St. Cloud 5...

139
00:13:46,432 --> 00:13:48,548
What is the number
of the Finley residence?

140
00:13:48,712 --> 00:13:50,304
Oh, no.

141
00:13:51,032 --> 00:13:53,626
Thanks. I'll call back later.

142
00:13:56,992 --> 00:13:58,664
Easy, princess.

143
00:13:59,272 --> 00:14:00,830
Who are you?

144
00:14:01,552 --> 00:14:03,190
- Help.
- Hush, now.

145
00:14:03,352 --> 00:14:06,662
- I had a terrible dream.
- Is all right, honey. Chance is with you.

146
00:14:06,832 --> 00:14:08,106
- Who?
- Me.

147
00:14:08,272 --> 00:14:09,990
I don't know who you are.

148
00:14:10,152 --> 00:14:12,746
Well, ill come back to you,
honey, as soon as...

149
00:14:12,912 --> 00:14:16,871
- What are you looking for?
- Oxygen mask.

150
00:14:17,032 --> 00:14:20,581
- You don't wanna overdo that oxygen...
- I need air. I can't breathe.

151
00:14:20,752 --> 00:14:22,185
Will you hurry? I'm dying.

152
00:14:23,392 --> 00:14:25,428
Hurry, right now.

153
00:14:25,752 --> 00:14:27,105
Will you come...!

154
00:14:54,192 --> 00:14:57,548
You leave me, please. Just leave me.

155
00:15:13,832 --> 00:15:16,221
Operator, give me St. Cloud 525.

156
00:15:24,112 --> 00:15:25,591
Cool drinks...

157
00:15:25,752 --> 00:15:28,186
...and some cookies.
- Thank you, ma'am.

158
00:15:28,352 --> 00:15:29,501
Finley residence.

159
00:15:30,112 --> 00:15:33,024
Miss Heavenly?
Who's calling her, please?

160
00:15:33,472 --> 00:15:34,825
Mr. Chance?

161
00:15:34,992 --> 00:15:38,780
I'm sorry, Mr. Chance,
but Miss Heavenly ain't...

162
00:15:39,872 --> 00:15:42,830
I don't know where she went.
All I know is, she ain't available.

163
00:15:42,992 --> 00:15:44,823
I'll take it, charles.

164
00:15:46,912 --> 00:15:48,664
Chance?

165
00:15:49,952 --> 00:15:51,544
Hello, honey.

166
00:15:52,232 --> 00:15:54,143
This is Aunt Nonnie.

167
00:15:54,552 --> 00:15:55,746
Wait.

168
00:15:55,912 --> 00:15:59,029
- Wait. Where are you?
- That phone call for me, Charles?

169
00:15:59,192 --> 00:16:03,424
- No, Mr. Tom.
- Hang up. I'll try to call you back.

170
00:16:03,592 --> 00:16:05,981
No, chance. No. Don't.

171
00:16:06,312 --> 00:16:07,791
Aunt Nonnie, I gotta see Heavenly.

172
00:16:07,952 --> 00:16:10,147
George Scudder was just here.
Did something happen?

173
00:16:10,432 --> 00:16:12,866
I'm terribly sorry, Mr. Bancroft.

174
00:16:13,032 --> 00:16:14,943
It is Mr. Bancroft, isn't it?

175
00:16:15,272 --> 00:16:17,069
Can't you talk now?

176
00:16:17,432 --> 00:16:20,071
Aunt Nonnie, have
Heavenly call me. Please.

177
00:16:20,472 --> 00:16:22,827
She can't. I'll call you back.

178
00:16:24,992 --> 00:16:27,711
Downstairs, in the cocktail lounge.
I'll wait.

179
00:16:30,072 --> 00:16:34,429
- You shouldn't have done that, Tom Jr.
- Aunt Nonnie, you're a silly old maid.

180
00:16:34,592 --> 00:16:36,662
And if he calls back, you just hang up.

181
00:16:37,552 --> 00:16:40,510
I mean it, Aunt Nonnie. Just hang up.

182
00:16:44,272 --> 00:16:45,625
Finley residence.

183
00:16:45,792 --> 00:16:47,589
No, Mr. Chance.

184
00:16:48,192 --> 00:16:49,386
She still ain't available.

185
00:16:49,552 --> 00:16:53,147
<i>We present this controversial
newsreel as a public service.</i>

186
00:16:53,352 --> 00:16:57,061
<i>In 1930, Tom Finley ran
for his first state office.</i>

187
00:16:57,232 --> 00:17:02,260
<i>You all know me. I'm just a
plain old dirt farmer, like you folks.</i>

188
00:17:02,592 --> 00:17:05,345
<i>And Tom Finley was elected.</i>

189
00:17:05,512 --> 00:17:07,980
<i>Tom Finley ran for governor.</i>

190
00:17:09,512 --> 00:17:11,901
<i>I'm against loose government...</i>

191
00:17:12,072 --> 00:17:15,428
<i>... loose money and loose women!</i>

192
00:17:15,592 --> 00:17:17,708
<i>And Tom Finley was elected.</i>

193
00:17:17,872 --> 00:17:21,706
<i>Tom Finley built a political machine
and became Boss Finley.</i>

194
00:17:21,872 --> 00:17:24,591
<i>He also built a
plain old dirt farmer's shack...</i>

195
00:17:24,752 --> 00:17:26,504
<i>... worth $300,000.</i>

196
00:17:26,672 --> 00:17:30,142
<i>He sails from his private beach
in his private speedboat.</i>

197
00:17:30,312 --> 00:17:34,430
<i>Boss Finley gave away
the offshore oil of his state.</i>

198
00:17:36,072 --> 00:17:38,745
<i>The oil man made Finley a partner...</i>

199
00:17:38,912 --> 00:17:42,382
<i>... and Boss Finley made his
oil partner the governor...</i>

200
00:17:42,552 --> 00:17:46,022
<i>... and kept him in office
all these years.</i>

201
00:17:46,192 --> 00:17:49,628
<i>Four months ago,
Professor Burtus Haven Smith...</i>

202
00:17:49,792 --> 00:17:51,862
<i>... ran against Finley's handpicked man.</i>

203
00:17:52,832 --> 00:17:55,869
<i>The only thing you have
to fear is Finley himself.</i>

204
00:17:56,032 --> 00:17:58,751
<i>Next day, Professor Smith, fired.</i>

205
00:17:58,912 --> 00:18:01,221
<i>His home was invaded by hoodlums...</i>

206
00:18:01,392 --> 00:18:04,350
<i>... books and paintings
burned on the lawn.</i>

207
00:18:05,152 --> 00:18:07,382
<i>Did you recognize any of them, sir?</i>

208
00:18:07,552 --> 00:18:11,227
<i>No. They wore masks like this.</i>

209
00:18:12,992 --> 00:18:15,711
<i>I found this button.</i>

210
00:18:22,432 --> 00:18:27,062
<i>Yes, sir. I'm president of the
Finley Youth Club, and I'm proud of it.</i>

211
00:18:27,232 --> 00:18:30,429
<i>But I don 't know nothing about
no book burnings or...</i>

212
00:18:30,592 --> 00:18:33,231
<i>This thing, it could be dropped
accidentally on purpose...</i>

213
00:18:33,392 --> 00:18:36,828
<i>...you know what I mean?
- But to date, there has been no probe...</i>

214
00:18:36,992 --> 00:18:39,665
<i>... no police action, no arrests.</i>

215
00:18:39,832 --> 00:18:41,788
<i>- Why?
- Shut that contraption off.</i>

216
00:18:42,432 --> 00:18:47,062
<i>These are the fruits
of Boss Finley's rise to power...</i>

217
00:18:48,392 --> 00:18:52,783
How can a Christian TV network
tolerate those filthy, black lies?

218
00:18:52,952 --> 00:18:55,625
- Right here, in the heart of America.
- Why, they ought to be...

219
00:18:55,792 --> 00:18:57,783
Thank you, honey.
- Horsewhipped and shot.

220
00:18:57,952 --> 00:19:01,149
And if I wasn't mayor and against
violence, I'd do it myself.

221
00:19:01,312 --> 00:19:03,872
Well, if that TV report lied,
why not sue them for libel?

222
00:19:04,032 --> 00:19:05,863
If they lied?

223
00:19:07,032 --> 00:19:08,784
You know, you surprise me, Ben.

224
00:19:08,952 --> 00:19:11,625
For a man who's smart enough
to run a big daily newspaper...

225
00:19:11,792 --> 00:19:14,750
<i>...you sure surprise me.
Can't you recognize New York...</i>

226
00:19:14,912 --> 00:19:17,062
...Red propaganda when you see it?

227
00:19:17,232 --> 00:19:19,348
Do you call that TV newsreel fair?

228
00:19:19,512 --> 00:19:21,548
Now, Maribelle,
we're all on the same side.

229
00:19:21,952 --> 00:19:25,069
- Are we, Ben?
- Fair, you mean?

230
00:19:25,392 --> 00:19:27,508
Well, your father's going
on the same network.

231
00:19:27,712 --> 00:19:31,068
Same time, same freedom of expression.
I'd say that was pretty fair.

232
00:19:31,232 --> 00:19:32,870
A lot fairer than burning books and...

233
00:19:33,032 --> 00:19:34,511
You accusing me, Ben?

234
00:19:34,952 --> 00:19:38,228
Why, Tom Jr. Hasn't got
a mean bone in his body.

235
00:19:39,552 --> 00:19:41,702
He might be a hot-blooded
buck like his daddy...

236
00:19:41,872 --> 00:19:44,545
<i>- Now, Mrs. Norris.
- ...but he'd never resort to violence.</i>

237
00:19:44,712 --> 00:19:47,863
Never. And you have my personal
guarantee that whoever did do it...

238
00:19:48,032 --> 00:19:49,351
