I figure you were victimized.

1184
01:23:08,579 --> 01:23:10,934
You're a rich, famous,
respected person, princess.

1185
01:23:11,099 --> 01:23:12,532
You don't want any trouble.

1186
01:23:12,699 --> 01:23:13,973
Thank you.

1187
01:23:14,139 --> 01:23:16,528
And now, if you are through
trying to frighten me...

1188
01:23:16,699 --> 01:23:19,930
...or shake me down, or whatever,
I would like to finish my breakfast.

1189
01:23:20,099 --> 01:23:21,452
Yes, ma'am. Go right ahead.

1190
01:23:21,619 --> 01:23:23,371
May I ask you
what Mr. Wayne is to you?

1191
01:23:23,539 --> 01:23:25,097
You may not.

1192
01:23:34,979 --> 01:23:40,531
<i>He's... He drives my car.
He's in my employ. He's my driver.</i>

1193
01:23:40,699 --> 01:23:42,451
What are you doing here in St. Cloud?

1194
01:23:43,699 --> 01:23:45,929
Okay, he brought you here. Why?

1195
01:23:46,099 --> 01:23:47,737
We're just passing through.

1196
01:23:47,899 --> 01:23:50,811
- Thas all.
- Well, fine. Just pass right on through.

1197
01:23:50,979 --> 01:23:53,447
But you tell that scum
to drive you out of here quick.

1198
01:23:54,019 --> 01:23:56,249
- On whose authority?
- Mine.

1199
01:23:56,419 --> 01:24:01,129
Well, even in this impossible place,
you couldn't represent the law.

1200
01:24:01,539 --> 01:24:04,007
There isn't any law
that covers the Chance Waynes.

1201
01:24:04,619 --> 01:24:07,372
Not after what he did to me
and to my family.

1202
01:24:07,539 --> 01:24:08,733
- What?
- You just never mind.

1203
01:24:08,899 --> 01:24:10,412
- What did he do?
- Never you mind.

1204
01:24:10,579 --> 01:24:13,093
<i>You tell him that I said
if he don't pass through...</i>

1205
01:24:13,259 --> 01:24:15,853
<i>...his life ain't worth spit in the wind.</i>

1206
01:24:19,979 --> 01:24:22,812
Well, sometime you come on back
and see us, hear?

1207
01:24:22,979 --> 01:24:24,970
We'll lay out the red carpet for you.

1208
01:24:25,579 --> 01:24:27,012
Okay?

1209
01:24:27,739 --> 01:24:29,616
Well, so long, Miss Del Lago.

1210
01:24:31,859 --> 01:24:35,374
Nightfall. Now, you and him
be gone by nightfall.

1211
01:24:35,539 --> 01:24:37,211
You hear me?

1212
01:25:04,379 --> 01:25:08,338
Oh, where? Where did he put it?

1213
01:25:09,659 --> 01:25:11,012
Where?

1214
01:25:14,299 --> 01:25:16,494
Oh, Chance.

1215
01:25:18,139 --> 01:25:19,857
Chance.

1216
01:25:21,139 --> 01:25:23,175
Operator.

1217
01:25:23,339 --> 01:25:27,696
Operator. I want a bottle of vodka
sent up here at once.

1218
01:25:27,859 --> 01:25:30,851
Yes. Well, then send me
a bottle of anything.

1219
01:25:31,019 --> 01:25:32,293
And operator?

1220
01:25:32,459 --> 01:25:36,338
Operator, I want you to find
Mr. Chance Wayne for me.

1221
01:25:36,739 --> 01:25:38,730
Well, page him.

1222
01:25:38,899 --> 01:25:42,938
And try that happy
cocktail bar of yours.

1223
01:25:44,739 --> 01:25:46,855
- Change for a quarter.
- Thank you.

1224
01:25:50,579 --> 01:25:53,298
Did you arrange to have that
prescription filled yet?

1225
01:25:53,459 --> 01:25:55,051
I'll check, Mr. Wayne.

1226
01:25:58,739 --> 01:26:01,014
Hello? Professor Smith?

1227
01:26:01,539 --> 01:26:05,498
You can't beat Boss Finley
by making speeches about God...

1228
01:26:05,659 --> 01:26:08,014
...or by heckling him about chastity...

1229
01:26:08,179 --> 01:26:11,057
...because the Boss has a patent
on that jazz.

1230
01:26:11,219 --> 01:26:13,335
He's a low-down hillbilly.

1231
01:26:13,499 --> 01:26:18,209
And it takes a hillbilly to cut down
a hillbilly, and thas me.

1232
01:26:20,259 --> 01:26:21,772
Don't bother about my name.

1233
01:26:21,939 --> 01:26:26,569
You just appear at that rally tonight
and ask him one question:

1234
01:26:27,059 --> 01:26:32,816
Why did Boss Finley make Dr. Scudder
chief of staff at the hospital?

1235
01:26:32,979 --> 01:26:35,812
Operator, are there any calls
for a Chance Wayne?

1236
01:26:37,419 --> 01:26:39,216
No, I mean outside calls.

1237
01:26:39,379 --> 01:26:41,131
Well, page me if there are, will you?

1238
01:26:41,299 --> 01:26:43,893
Chance?
Chance "High-Stepping" Wayne.

1239
01:26:44,059 --> 01:26:45,617
Hey, hey, Miss Lucy.

1240
01:26:45,779 --> 01:26:50,011
Honey, you used to be so attractive,
I couldn't stand it.

1241
01:26:50,179 --> 01:26:54,058
Now I can. Almost stand it.

1242
01:26:54,219 --> 01:26:57,609
Well, boy, you still look like
a million dollars, there, Miss Lucy.

1243
01:26:57,779 --> 01:26:59,770
Confederate money.

1244
01:27:00,499 --> 01:27:03,411
Hey, a year ago you would have
laughed at that.

1245
01:27:03,579 --> 01:27:06,013
- Well, I must be faint with thirst.
- Thirsty? Here?

1246
01:27:06,179 --> 01:27:09,694
Don't you know this is the land of
Bourbon, Sodom and Gomorrah Finley?

1247
01:27:09,859 --> 01:27:12,134
- Can I help you, Miss Lucy?
- Yeah. Drop dead.

1248
01:27:12,299 --> 01:27:13,778
What happened to your finger?

1249
01:27:13,939 --> 01:27:17,614
It got caught in your big,
fat blabbermouth.

1250
01:27:17,779 --> 01:27:19,576
Hey, honey, you wanna laugh?

1251
01:27:19,739 --> 01:27:24,017
Listen. Last night, Finley gave me this
for an Easter gift.

1252
01:27:24,179 --> 01:27:27,012
Well, he has always been generous.

1253
01:27:27,179 --> 01:27:28,692
Well, thas not all he gave me.

1254
01:27:28,859 --> 01:27:31,578
He gave me the treatment,
the full Finley treatment.

1255
01:27:31,739 --> 01:27:35,288
Ending up canceling my rooms,
my credit and my welcome.

1256
01:27:35,459 --> 01:27:39,054
And this morning, I was handed a ticket
to New Orleans. One way.

1257
01:27:39,219 --> 01:27:44,293
Well, that man has an irresistible passion
to see other people traveling.

1258
01:27:44,459 --> 01:27:46,575
Does he know you're back in town?

1259
01:27:46,739 --> 01:27:49,173
I would say he is
aware of my presence.

1260
01:27:50,299 --> 01:27:52,017
Whas in the pill, honey?

1261
01:27:52,179 --> 01:27:55,410
Well, when you are having fun,
this makes you have even more.

1262
01:27:56,939 --> 01:27:58,895
Are you? Having fun?

1263
01:27:59,059 --> 01:28:01,129
Baby, I'm having a ball.

1264
01:28:03,299 --> 01:28:07,929
Honey, I'm an expert
at pretending to have fun.

1265
01:28:08,099 --> 01:28:11,375
You are having a wake, not a ball.

1266
01:28:11,539 --> 01:28:14,258
Mr. Wayne? Phone, Mr. Wayne.

1267
01:28:19,899 --> 01:28:21,855
Isn't that Alexandra Del Lago?

1268
01:28:22,899 --> 01:28:24,332
Who?

1269
01:28:26,299 --> 01:28:29,496
Oh, Aunt Nonnie.
Yeah, is me, chance.

1270
01:28:29,659 --> 01:28:32,492
Miss Del Lago, will you
autograph this for me, please?

1271
01:28:32,659 --> 01:28:36,095
- I'm sorry.
- Not for me, for my little girl.

1272
01:28:36,979 --> 01:28:40,494
- Just write, "To my dearest Josephine."
- I'm looking for my glasses.

1273
01:28:41,139 --> 01:28:42,936
- Miss Del Lago, please.
- Some other time.

1274
01:28:43,099 --> 01:28:46,171
<i>- Tell Heavenly that I will be there.
- You shouldn't be seen here...</i>

1275
01:28:46,339 --> 01:28:48,330
...in this condition.
- Chance. Chance!

1276
01:28:54,899 --> 01:28:56,491
Get this drunken bum out of here.

1277
01:28:56,659 --> 01:28:58,809
Hey, hey, relax!

1278
01:28:59,939 --> 01:29:01,452
Relax, buster.

1279
01:29:01,619 --> 01:29:03,052
Chance.

1280
01:29:04,699 --> 01:29:07,532
- You all right, princess?
- Oh, Chance.

1281
01:29:08,619 --> 01:29:11,133
If you'd stayed upstairs,
that would not have happened.

1282
01:29:11,299 --> 01:29:13,654
- Oh, I did. I stayed.
- I told you to wait.

1283
01:29:13,819 --> 01:29:17,289
I waited. I waited forever.
But then a young man...

1284
01:29:17,459 --> 01:29:19,529
Princess, not now.
I've gotta do something.

1285
01:29:19,699 --> 01:29:21,610
Will you just wait upstairs?

1286
01:29:21,779 --> 01:29:22,973
Chance.

1287
01:29:23,499 --> 01:29:25,888
Chance, listen to me.
We've got to go away from here.

1288
01:29:26,059 --> 01:29:27,777
Princess, please, I haven't got time.

1289
01:29:27,939 --> 01:29:30,373
We'll just pretend that we're going
for a drive.

1290
01:29:30,539 --> 01:29:32,894
- Yeah, but...
- We'll forget about the bags.

1291
01:29:33,059 --> 01:29:35,619
I had a visitor, looking for you.

1292
01:29:35,779 --> 01:29:39,215
He was a horrible, vicious young man
with evil in his heart.

1293
01:29:39,379 --> 01:29:43,054
<i>And he said that if we weren't
out of town by nightfall, he'd...</i>

1294
01:29:43,219 --> 01:29:45,210
Oh, chance, I didn't know
where to find you.

1295
01:29:45,379 --> 01:29:48,496
And at first I felt panicky,
and then I got a little high again.

1296
01:29:48,659 --> 01:29:50,377
- I'm sorry.
- Look, I know, princess...

1297
01:29:50,539 --> 01:29:52,530
...but I gotta go now.
- Oh, Chance.

1298
01:29:52,699 --> 01:29:55,577
Chance, Chance, let me tell you.

1299
01:29:55,739 --> 01:29:58,890
Let me tell you the strange and
wonderful thing that happened to me.

1300
01:29:59,059 --> 01:30:03,291
<i>I realized that your coming back here
and the things that you'd hoped for...</i>

1301
01:30:03,459 --> 01:30:08,897
...poor baby, I knew that your comeback
had been a failure, like my own.

1302
01:30:09,059 --> 01:30:14,736
And at that moment,
I felt something in my heart for you.

1303
01:30:14,899 --> 01:30:19,290
Is a miracle. Is a wonderful thing
that has happened to me.

1304
01:30:19,459 --> 01:30:23,008
I felt something for somebody
besides myself.

1305
01:30:23,179 --> 01:30:24,737
You know what that means?

1306
01:30:24,899 --> 01:30:29,814
That means that my heart is still alive.
Still alive, Chance.

1307
01:30:30,699 --> 01:30:32,815
Well, you've got a wise heart,
princess.

1308
01:30:33,939 --> 01:30:36,897
Oh, I need you.
And we need each other.

1309
01:30:37,059 --> 01:30:40,972
We'll help each other.
You won't find me ungrateful.

1310
01:30:41,139 --> 01:30:45,291
Chance, I am truly ashamed
of last night.

1311
01:30:45,459 --> 01:30:49,577
I will never degrade you...

1312
01:30:49,739 --> 01:30:51,092
...nor myself.

1313
01:30:51,259 --> 01:30:54,012
I understand. Now, please, princess.

1314
01:30:54,179 --> 01:30:55,373
You want a screen test?

1315
01:30:58,939 --> 01:31:01,453
You'll have your test.
I'll honor that contract.

1316
01:31:01,619 --> 01:31:03,849
I'll make it good.
I'll make it even better.

1317
01:31:04,019 --> 01:31:08,171
Oh, princess, you are a glorious,
beautiful, lovely...

1318
01:31:08,339 --> 01:31:11,536
Monster. Drive, baby, drive.

1319
01:31:11,699 --> 01:31:14,213
Break every speed law from here...

1320
01:31:16,499 --> 01:31:18,455
No. No, baby.

1321
01:31:18,619 --> 01:31:22,612
- Princess, I got unfinished business.
- Don't leave me again. Not now.

1322
01:31:22,779 --> 01:31:24,531
- I got to.
- Chance!

1323
01:31:25,179 --> 01:31:27,010
Chance.

1324
01:31:30,939 --> 01:31:34,409
Chance, you'll never come back.
They'll cut the life out of you.

1325
01:31:34,579 --> 01:31:38,891
- Princess, go up to the room and wait.
- No, please. Please, baby.

1326
01:31:39,059 --> 01:31:40,492
I can't be alone now.

1327
01:31:40,659 --> 01:31:43,332
Don't ask me to stay. Please.

1328
01:31:43,499 --> 01:31:45,057
Just give me this one last break.

1329
01:31:45,219 --> 01:31:49,451
Oh, Chance. Chance. Chance!

1330
01:31:55,299 --> 01:31:57,688
Don't send me back
to that room alone.

1331
01:31:57,859 --> 01:31:59,850
We could both do
with some comfort, honey.

1332
01:32:00,019 --> 01:32:02,692
Southern Comfort, 100 proof?

1333
01:32:02,859 --> 01:32:04,178
Thank you, miss.

1334
01:32:04,339 --> 01:32:07,172
Give the hicks a show, miss.

1335
01:32:07,339 --> 01:32:12,333
You show them you're a real princess.
Is good public relations.

1336
01:32:12,499 --> 01:32:18,256
Public? The public and I have always
enjoyed the very best relations.

1337
01:32:26,219 --> 01:32:27,811
Hi there.

1338
01:32:28,859 --> 01:32:32,647
Wouldn't you like to have a nice,
cool dip before lunch?

1339
01:32:40,219 --> 01:32:42,938
- Don't you go away, now.
- No, ma'am.

1340
01:33:11,059 --> 01:33:12,253
No.

1341
01:33:12,419 --> 01:33:15,331
Dear, she shouldn't have gone anywhere
without you, should she?

1342
01:33:15,499 --> 01:33:16,978
No, ma'am, she shouldn't have.

1343
01:33:58,059 --> 01:34:02,098
Go away, Chance. Go away.
Leave here. Leave St. Cloud.

1344
01:34:02,259 --> 01:34:05,296
- Well, yeah, we'll leave here together.
- Is too late for that.

1345
01:34:05,459 --> 01:34:08,417
Baby, is just the beginning for us.

1346
01:34:08,579 --> 01:34:12,128
Now, no more next time.
This time, is for keeps.

1347
01:34:13,219 --> 01:34:14,857
We got it made, baby.

1348
01:34:15,019 --> 01:34:19,217
This is my passport out of here.
Right to the top, nonstop.

1349
01:34:19,419 --> 01:34:21,216
Let go, Chance.

1350
01:34:21,379 --> 01:34:22,607
Let go of my life.

1351
01:34:23,379 --> 01:34:26,928
But, baby, the door is opened.
This is a contract!

1352
01:34:27,379 --> 01:34:30,496
Now, is witnessed and notarized
and signed by Alexandra Del Lago.

1353
01:34:30,659 --> 01:34:34,254
She's my patroness.
She's my agent, my producer.

1354
01:34:34,419 --> 01:34:35,613
This is on the level.

1355
01:34:35,779 --> 01:34:37,929
- You've gotta believe me!
- I believe you.

1356
01:34:38,099 --> 01:34:40,090
All right, then. We'll leave here.
Together.

1357
01:34:40,259 --> 01:34:43,376
You and me and Princess Del Lago.
Tonight. Whenever you say.

1358
01:34:43,539 --> 01:34:45,450
Take your princess and go away.

1359
01:34:45,619 --> 01:34:48,292
Now. Before tonight.

1360
01:34:48,459 --> 01:34:50,177
You want me
to leave here without you?

1361
01:34:50,339 --> 01:34:52,216
Don't come back.

1362
01:34:52,379 --> 01:34:54,609
Don't call anymore. Run!

1363
01:34:54,779 --> 01:34:57,930
But, baby, what about you?
What about you and me?

1364
01:34:58,099 --> 01:35:00,055
Forget about me!

1365
01:35:00,219 --> 01:35:02,972
You want me to forget
that you're carrying my baby?

1366
01:35:03,139 --> 01:35:05,937
Yes! The way I had to forget!

1367
01:35:06,339 --> 01:35:08,409
Go back to your dream!

1368
01:35:33,059 --> 01:35:35,254
- You got the loudspeaker tested?
- Yeah.

1369
01:35:35,419 --> 01:35:37,774
- How about the TV setup? Okay?
- Yeah. Okay.

1370
01:35:40,459 --> 01:35:43,132
- I want you to stand by for a surprise.
- What kind of surprise?

1371
01:35:43,299 --> 01:35:46,097
I don't know. I got an anonymous
phone call, so just stand by.

1372
01:35:46,259 --> 01:35:48,011
Yes, ma'am, princess!

1373
01:35:48,179 --> 01:35:51,251
Honey,
get the bill ready for suite 212.

1374
01:35:51,419 --> 01:35:54,889
- Miss Lucy, your bill's been paid in full.
- Thas what you think.

1375
01:36:04,259 --> 01:36:07,376
- Hold on.
- Tom Jr., they're checking out.

1376
01:36:07,539 --> 01:36:10,497
The princess lady
just asked for the bill.

1377
01:36:48,819 --> 01:36:50,935
Come here.
You just had to see him, didn't you?

1378
01:36:51,099 --> 01:36:54,250
You just naturally had to lay
in chance Wayne's arms like a trollop.

1379
01:37:04,659 --> 01:37:07,378
Folks, my daughter!

1380
01:37:09,139 --> 01:37:11,778
Who says purity and politics
don't go together?

1381
01:37:29,779 --> 01:37:31,337
Well!

1382
01:37:31,539 --> 01:37:33,928
I thought,
from the happy celebration...

1383
01:37:34,099 --> 01:37:38,934
...that you were being served on a platter
with an apple stuck in your mouth.

1384
01:37:40,699 --> 01:37:42,655
- What are you doing?
- Getting out of here.

1385
01:37:42,819 --> 01:37:46,414
- As fast as your car will take us.
- Oh, well. I have another driver.

1386
01:37:46,579 --> 01:37:48,854
A certain Miss Lucy.

1387
01:37:49,019 --> 01:37:52,694
A kindly soul who will drive me
out of this hellish nightmare...

1388
01:37:52,859 --> 01:37:54,338
...as far as New Orleans.

1389
01:37:54,499 --> 01:37:57,297
I'm still your driver, princess.
We're leaving here together.

1390
01:37:57,459 --> 01:38:00,337
What happened
to your unfinished business?

1391
01:38:00,499 --> 01:38:02,569
Floppola?

1392
01:38:05,739 --> 01:38:09,448
- Well, I'm back. Isn't that enough?
- In a word, no.

1393
01:38:11,939 --> 01:38:14,817
- Oh, princess, baby...
- No!

1394
01:38:15,699 --> 01:38:17,735
Don't answer that.

1395
01:38:17,899 --> 01:38:19,127
Chance!

1396
01:38:19,579 --> 01:38:20,978
- Hello?
- I told you not to.

1397
01:38:21,139 --> 01:38:24,051
- Who's calling the princess?
- Will you please, please hang up?

1398
01:38:24,219 --> 01:38:27,211
Is Walter Winchell, in Hollywood.

1399
01:38:28,019 --> 01:38:29,930
Oh, no.

1400
01:38:30,699 --> 01:38:32,496
- Oh, no.
- Yeah, put him on.

1401
01:38:32,659 --> 01:38:34,729
- No. No!
- Yeah, she's right here.

1402
01:38:34,899 --> 01:38:37,811
Oh, how did he find me? How?

1403
01:38:38,379 --> 01:38:40,654
- It was you.
- Hello? Hello, Mr. Winchell?

1404
01:38:40,819 --> 01:38:44,016
Oh, yes.
Well, this is Chance Wayne speaking.

1405
01:38:44,179 --> 01:38:45,931
I called for the
Princess Kosmonopolis.

1406
01:38:46,099 --> 01:38:47,373
Alexandra...!

1407
01:38:47,539 --> 01:38:49,689
I mean, Alexandra Del Lago.
Last night?

1408
01:38:49,859 --> 01:38:51,053
Oh, yeah. She's fine, fine.

1409
01:38:51,219 --> 01:38:54,768
She just wanted to tell you about
this new star that she's discovered.

1410
01:38:55,019 --> 01:38:57,214
- Oh, sure, she can talk for herself.
- I can't.

1411
01:38:57,379 --> 01:39:01,452
- Princess, come on. He's waiting.
- Well, you tell him that I am dying.

1412
01:39:01,619 --> 01:39:02,813
And I just might.

1413
01:39:02,979 --> 01:39:04,856
You gotta meet it halfway.

1414
01:39:07,579 --> 01:39:09,376
Princess?

1415
01:39:17,099 --> 01:39:18,851
Walter?

1416
01:39:20,459 --> 01:39:21,608
Walter?

1417
01:39:22,059 --> 01:39:26,849
Walter! Well, is that really you, Waldo?

1418
01:39:27,499 --> 01:39:31,128
Yes, yes, is me. Alexandra.

1419
01:39:31,299 --> 01:39:33,130
Thas whas left of me.

1420
01:39:33,499 --> 01:39:34,978
Walter?

1421
01:39:35,139 --> 01:39:38,654
Oh, yes, yes, I did go to the preview,
but I only stayed a few minutes.

1422
01:39:38,819 --> 01:39:45,054
As soon I saw that first big close-up of
myself on that monstrous CinemaScope...

1423
01:39:45,219 --> 01:39:47,130
...I tell you, I ran right out of there!

1424
01:39:47,299 --> 01:39:49,938
I screamed for a taxi,
and I haven't been...

1425
01:39:50,099 --> 01:39:52,135
I haven't stopped running since.

1426
01:39:52,499 --> 01:39:53,648
What?

1427
01:39:53,819 --> 01:39:59,018
Oh, no, no. No, no, I heard nothing,
read nothing, I just wanted oblivion.

1428
01:39:59,179 --> 01:40:00,817
What?

1429
01:40:02,579 --> 01:40:04,456
Walter.

1430
01:40:05,139 --> 01:40:07,130
You're just being kind, aren't you?

1431
01:40:07,299 --> 01:40:09,096
Princess, tell him
about my screen test.

1432
01:40:10,259 --> 01:40:14,047
- One moment, Walter, I'm breathless.
- Tell him to break it in his column...

1433
01:40:14,219 --> 01:40:18,371
Go in the bathroom and stick
your head under cold water.

1434
01:40:18,539 --> 01:40:21,736
Walter, now, tell me,
do you really think so?

1435
01:40:21,899 --> 01:40:26,814
You're not just being kind,
are you, because of old times?

1436
01:40:27,539 --> 01:40:33,296
Grown, did you say? My talent?
Well, in what way, Walter?

1437
01:40:33,459 --> 01:40:34,858
- More depth?
- Tell him about me.

1438
01:40:35,019 --> 01:40:36,975
- More what? What did you say?
- Me.

1439
01:40:37,139 --> 01:40:38,572
More power?

1440
01:40:38,739 --> 01:40:42,618
- Well, God bless you. God bless you!
- Come on, now, cut the chatter.

1441
01:40:42,779 --> 01:40:45,816
Tell him you've found a new
leading man with a bright new future.

1442
01:40:45,979 --> 01:40:49,654
Walter, that is very,
very sweet of you.

1443
01:40:49,819 --> 01:40:53,858
I don't even care if you're not altogether
sincere in that statement, Walter...

1444
01:40:54,019 --> 01:40:58,695
...because I think you know what
the past 15 years have been like.

1445
01:40:58,859 --> 01:41:00,577
What?

1446
01:41:01,619 --> 01:41:04,179
Whas that, Walter?

1447
01:41:04,979 --> 01:41:07,174
They want me?

1448
01:41:09,939 --> 01:41:12,976
They really want me?

1449
01:41:13,979 --> 01:41:16,493
Well, for what part?

1450
01:41:16,659 --> 01:41:19,332
Who? Who wants me?

1451
01:41:23,099 --> 01:41:25,294
Oh, dear Lord.

1452
01:41:33,299 --> 01:41:35,529
Walter!

1453
01:41:36,179 --> 01:41:39,012
Walter, please excuse me.

1454
01:41:39,179 --> 01:41:42,649
No, no. Excuse me. I'm crying, dear,
and I haven't got any Kleenex.

1455
01:41:42,819 --> 01:41:44,537
Come on, talk to him about me.

1456
01:41:44,699 --> 01:41:46,849
- Oh, Walter...
- Me, me, me!

1457
01:41:47,499 --> 01:41:49,296
Walter, what?

1458
01:41:49,459 --> 01:41:51,450
No, no, I didn't read the reviews.

1459
01:41:51,619 --> 01:41:54,656
Newspapers.
Who cares what the newspapers say?

1460
01:41:54,819 --> 01:41:59,688
What did they say? Tell me.
Tell me word for word.

1461
01:42:09,539 --> 01:42:14,249
Before the festivities, let us all
bow our heads in silent prayer.

1462
01:42:14,419 --> 01:42:18,173
Mrs. Maribelle Norris
will sing while we pray.

1463
01:42:29,339 --> 01:42:30,533
Good night, professor.

1464
01:42:30,699 --> 01:42:32,655
Can't we do this
without hurting the girl?

1465
01:42:32,819 --> 01:42:34,889
Do you wanna get rid
of Boss Finley or not?

1466
01:42:40,499 --> 01:42:42,854
Yes. Oh, no!

1467
01:42:43,019 --> 01:42:49,015
<i>Oh, Walter, the New Yorker magazine
praised it.</i>

1468
01:42:49,179 --> 01:42:53,934
Oh, I'm too overwhelmed. I'm...
Walter, I'll have to call you back later.

1469
01:42:54,099 --> 01:42:56,772
- I can't believe it. I can't believe it.
- Hello?

1470
01:42:56,939 --> 01:43:03,014
My picture has broken box-office records
in New York and L.A.

1471
01:43:03,179 --> 01:43:05,647
<i>- Get him back on this phone.
- Variety says...</i>

1472
01:43:05,819 --> 01:43:09,494
...that I am the biggest boff
in release today.

1473
01:43:09,659 --> 01:43:12,776
- Princess, I took care of you.
- I've gotta go to a clinic for a week.

1474
01:43:12,939 --> 01:43:14,816
- I delivered my end.
- A week or 10 days.

1475
01:43:14,979 --> 01:43:17,129
Would you shut up and listen!

1476
01:43:17,299 --> 01:43:22,327
Bennie. I'll have to get him to cover up
my tracks these past few weeks in hell.

1477
01:43:22,499 --> 01:43:24,171
- Get Winchell back on this phone.
- What?

1478
01:43:24,339 --> 01:43:25,613
Tell him about me!

1479
01:43:25,779 --> 01:43:29,089
What? Tell him about a beach boy
that I picked up for pleasure...

1480
01:43:29,259 --> 01:43:31,136
...a distraction from panic?

1481
01:43:31,299 --> 01:43:34,848
Now? Now, when the
nightmare is over?

1482
01:43:35,019 --> 01:43:38,489
And involve my name
with the name of a...

1483
01:43:38,659 --> 01:43:40,650
A blackmailer.

1484
01:43:40,819 --> 01:43:43,094
You've just been using me. Using me.

1485
01:43:43,259 --> 01:43:47,696
When you ran out on me downstairs,
you ran out on this contract too.

1486
01:43:47,859 --> 01:43:53,855
Just a short while ago, I needed you.
Oh, how I needed you.

1487
01:43:54,019 --> 01:43:58,171
Well, now I need nobody.

1488
01:43:58,339 --> 01:43:59,692
I climbed up alone.

1489
01:43:59,859 --> 01:44:04,057
And I will climb back alone.
Back to where I belong.

1490
01:44:04,219 --> 01:44:08,337
I will live alone and I will work alone.

1491
01:44:08,499 --> 01:44:13,095
I know exactly the kind
of gold-plated hell I'm going to.

1492
01:44:13,259 --> 01:44:19,016
But you, you have gone past something
you couldn't afford to go past.

1493
01:44:19,179 --> 01:44:22,728
Your time, your youth.
You've passed it.

1494
01:44:22,899 --> 01:44:24,890
Is all you've had, and you've had it!

1495
01:44:25,059 --> 01:44:27,050
Look who's talking.

1496
01:44:27,219 --> 01:44:29,574
Just look at yourself.

1497
01:44:30,979 --> 01:44:33,732
What do you see in there?

1498
01:44:35,859 --> 01:44:38,214
I see me.

1499
01:44:38,379 --> 01:44:43,328
Alexandra Del Lago, artist and star.

1500
01:44:43,499 --> 01:44:45,615
Now you look at yourself.

1501
01:44:45,779 --> 01:44:47,417
What do you see?

1502
01:44:47,579 --> 01:44:49,217
What?

1503
01:44:49,379 --> 01:44:53,452
A nameless face, thas what you see.
Oh, I remember faces like yours.

1504
01:44:53,859 --> 01:44:56,737
I remember young men
with dreams like yours.

1505
01:44:56,899 --> 01:44:59,493
I remember their eyes,
I remember their voices...

1506
01:44:59,659 --> 01:45:02,571
...I remember their smiles,
I remember their bodies.

1507
01:45:02,739 --> 01:45:07,051
But their names, their names have gone.
They're just nameless bodies.

1508
01:45:07,219 --> 01:45:09,130
Well, you remind me
of one in particular.

1509
01:45:09,299 --> 01:45:12,530
What was his name? Franz something.
Franz, Franz...

1510
01:45:12,979 --> 01:45:18,611
- Albertzart. Yes, Franz Albertzart.
- Are you through? Have you finished?

1511
01:45:18,779 --> 01:45:22,488
I saw Franz a few years
later in Monte Carlo.

1512
01:45:22,659 --> 01:45:27,050
He was with a woman of 70,
and his eyes were older than hers.

1513
01:45:27,219 --> 01:45:28,811
But she held him.

1514
01:45:28,979 --> 01:45:33,097
She led him by an invisible chain
through a string of hotels...

1515
01:45:33,259 --> 01:45:37,457
...and casinos and bars
like a blind, obedient lap dog.

1516
01:45:37,939 --> 01:45:42,171
Chance Wayne is Franz Albertzart.

1517
01:45:45,179 --> 01:45:48,808
Oh, no. Look, I'm not Franz anybody.
Princess, I'm your next leading man.

1518
01:45:50,259 --> 01:45:54,855
Princess, now, look, you've gotta
open the right doors for me.

1519
01:45:55,019 --> 01:45:56,737
I know you're gonna do this for me.

1520
01:45:56,899 --> 01:46:00,369
I have been knocking on those doors
of success till my insides are bloody.

1521
01:46:00,539 --> 01:46:03,611
Thas how I've been knocking
on those doors, with my bare insides.

1522
01:46:03,779 --> 01:46:05,132
You will open only one door:

1523
01:46:05,299 --> 01:46:08,097
The door to my car as my chauffeur.

1524
01:46:08,259 --> 01:46:09,897
You will wake me in the morning...

1525
01:46:10,059 --> 01:46:13,688
...as my butler or my lover,
depending on what I want.

1526
01:46:13,859 --> 01:46:16,578
In a few years, you will be through
with your good looks...

1527
01:46:16,739 --> 01:46:18,491
...and I will be through with you.

1528
01:46:18,659 --> 01:46:21,696
And that is the truth.
Can you face the truth?

1529
01:46:22,099 --> 01:46:26,331
Are you ready to be my chauffeur?
My next Franz Albertzart?

1530
01:46:26,499 --> 01:46:28,729
Oh, don't you know I would die first?

1531
01:46:29,579 --> 01:46:32,651
I would. I would rather die first.

1532
01:46:34,579 --> 01:46:38,413
And here he is.
May the good Lord protect him.

1533
01:46:38,619 --> 01:46:40,735
Our Tom.

1534
01:46:49,099 --> 01:46:54,890
I am here to answer charges against
my good name and character.

1535
01:46:57,299 --> 01:46:59,688
Thirty years ago,
the voice of God told me...

1536
01:46:59,859 --> 01:47:02,134
...to save this sweet land
from pollution.

1537
01:47:02,299 --> 01:47:08,534
Well, I am here on the same
sacred mission tonight.

1538
01:47:09,259 --> 01:47:12,888
To save us from outsiders
who wanna corrupt our way of life.

1539
01:47:13,059 --> 01:47:14,253
Boss Finley!

1540
01:47:14,419 --> 01:47:16,808
Hey, Boss Finley!

1541
01:47:16,979 --> 01:47:19,368
What way of life you talking about?

1542
01:47:19,539 --> 01:47:21,609
You mean the way your daughter...

1543
01:47:21,779 --> 01:47:25,931
The way your virtuous Miss Heavenly
had a secret operation...

1544
01:47:26,099 --> 01:47:28,613
...at the hands of Dr. Scudder?
- What are you waiting for?

1545
01:47:28,779 --> 01:47:32,567
An illegal operation,
performed in your hospital.

1546
01:47:32,739 --> 01:47:34,889
Aided and abetted by you.

1547
01:47:35,059 --> 01:47:38,495
- And forced on her without her consent.
- That is a dirty, black lie!

1548
01:47:38,659 --> 01:47:41,127
- Did God tell you how to rob us blind?
- Show yourself!

1549
01:47:41,299 --> 01:47:45,451
- Listen to me, folks!
- How to use your office for gain?

1550
01:47:45,619 --> 01:47:48,372
- Listen to me!
- Come on, get him out of here!

1551
01:47:48,539 --> 01:47:51,576
I have dedicated my life to God,
home and country.

1552
01:47:52,259 --> 01:47:54,454
My life is an open book.

1553
01:47:55,059 --> 01:47:58,335
Listen to me, folks!
Folks, listen to me!

1554
01:48:05,339 --> 01:48:08,490
Chance, we're leaving.
Right now. Together.

1555
01:48:08,659 --> 01:48:12,174
Murderer! Baby killer!

1556
01:48:13,379 --> 01:48:15,415
I'm going to send a boy
up for my luggage.

1557
01:48:15,579 --> 01:48:18,093
You had better come down
with my luggage.

1558
01:48:18,259 --> 01:48:20,250
- I am not part of your luggage.
- Chance.

1559
01:48:20,419 --> 01:48:24,412
Whatever I am,
I am not part of your luggage.

1560
01:48:26,099 --> 01:48:30,251
All right. You know whas going
to happen to you if you stay.

1561
01:48:30,419 --> 01:48:32,330
Goodbye.

1562
01:48:35,979 --> 01:48:37,128
Chance.

1563
01:48:37,659 --> 01:48:42,096
<i>Chance, dear, I... Well, is...</i>

1564
01:48:43,419 --> 01:48:48,334
- You forget something, princess?
- Well, yes. Yes, I did.

1565
01:48:52,819 --> 01:48:55,538
- These, maybe?
- Oh, yes.

1566
01:48:56,299 --> 01:48:58,369
Of course, last night
they were worthless...

1567
01:48:58,539 --> 01:49:01,212
...but now, after my comeback...

1568
01:49:01,379 --> 01:49:05,213
...you know,
they're worth a small jackpot.

1569
01:49:05,379 --> 01:49:08,815
- In cash.
- On the house.

1570
01:49:09,459 --> 01:49:14,294
Chance. Please, let me help you.

1571
01:49:14,459 --> 01:49:16,654
- Goodbye, lover.
- At least let me take you away.

1572
01:49:16,819 --> 01:49:19,128
- And good luck.
- I'll wait for you in the car.

1573
01:49:19,299 --> 01:49:23,895
Princess, each of us has his own
private hell to go to.

1574
01:49:32,259 --> 01:49:33,851
- Find your sister.
- Take it easy, Pa.

1575
01:49:34,019 --> 01:49:36,010
She'll run off with that punk.

1576
01:49:36,179 --> 01:49:39,728
- No, he's gone. Checked out.
- That won't stop her.

1577
01:49:40,459 --> 01:49:42,177
Will you let me handle this?

1578
01:49:46,099 --> 01:49:47,373
Mr. Finley.

1579
01:49:47,539 --> 01:49:49,211
How would you
answer the charges...?

1580
01:49:49,379 --> 01:49:52,132
I am shocked, shocked,
to find our state overrun...

1581
01:49:52,299 --> 01:49:55,177
...by backstabbing Bolsheviki
and Red rabble-rousers.

1582
01:49:55,339 --> 01:49:56,818
Get the governor on the phone.

1583
01:49:56,979 --> 01:50:00,892
Are you aware it was the Finley Youth
Club hoodlums that started that riot?

1584
01:50:01,299 --> 01:50:02,493
What riot?

1585
01:50:02,659 --> 01:50:06,447
I'm only aware that decent Americans
were defending freedom of speech...

1586
01:50:06,619 --> 01:50:08,894
...which I have yet
to receive the benefit of.

1587
01:50:09,059 --> 01:50:11,778
Oh, Miss Finley,
would you care to make a statement?

1588
01:50:12,819 --> 01:50:14,969
- Miss Finley?
- Hasn't enough been said already?

1589
01:50:15,139 --> 01:50:19,849
Sure, Aunt Nonnie, folks will think
we got something to hide.

1590
01:50:20,779 --> 01:50:22,974
Sugar? Heavenly, baby.

1591
01:50:23,459 --> 01:50:26,656
Precious, your papa's talking to you.

1592
01:50:26,979 --> 01:50:28,651
You came here
of your own free will...

1593
01:50:28,819 --> 01:50:32,858
...and I hereby give you just as much
freedom to speak your piece, right now.

1594
01:50:33,219 --> 01:50:34,811
Take me home, Papa.

1595
01:50:34,979 --> 01:50:37,288
Good night, folks. Good night, you-all.

1596
01:50:46,419 --> 01:50:48,330
Heavenly!

1597
01:50:50,419 --> 01:50:52,091
Heavenly!

1598
01:50:54,179 --> 01:50:56,534
Mr. Chance, is me, charles.

1599
01:50:57,259 --> 01:50:59,375
Don't stay here, Mr. Chance. Don't!

1600
01:50:59,939 --> 01:51:01,895
Don't stay here.

1601
01:51:02,659 --> 01:51:04,536
Please, Mr. Chance,
don't stay here now.

1602
01:51:05,219 --> 01:51:07,255
Heavenly!

1603
01:51:22,819 --> 01:51:24,855
Well, lookie here.

1604
01:51:25,019 --> 01:51:29,649
Thought you'd be halfway to california
by now with that tramp actress of yours.

1605
01:51:30,459 --> 01:51:32,415
Heavenly!

1606
01:51:32,579 --> 01:51:36,128
Don't you ever speak the name
of my sister again.

1607
01:51:38,539 --> 01:51:40,655
Heavenly...

1608
01:51:43,059 --> 01:51:45,050
Heavenly!

1609
01:52:11,379 --> 01:52:13,017
- Don't you know?
- Kill him.

1610
01:52:13,179 --> 01:52:17,934
No. Just gonna take away
lover-boy's meal ticket.

1611
01:52:18,099 --> 01:52:19,851
Put him down there.

1612
01:52:30,939 --> 01:52:32,816
Chance?

1613
01:52:35,419 --> 01:52:37,216
Chance.

1614
01:52:47,779 --> 01:52:49,929
Bring him over here.

1615
01:52:55,419 --> 01:52:57,535
Look at yourself.

1616
01:53:01,699 --> 01:53:04,293
No woman will ever again
pay to love that.

1617
01:53:24,739 --> 01:53:27,207
- Chance?
- Go in the house.

1618
01:53:27,379 --> 01:53:29,609
Hello? Yes, ma'am, just a moment.

1619
01:53:29,779 --> 01:53:31,531
Pa, phone. Governor calling.

1620
01:53:35,899 --> 01:53:39,289
- Chance?
- Hello, governor. How's the family?

1621
01:53:39,459 --> 01:53:42,576
- Fine, fine.
- Night, Aunt Nonnie.

1622
01:53:45,939 --> 01:53:50,615
Oh, baby, what did we do to you?

1623
01:53:58,179 --> 01:54:00,249
Don't cry.

1624
01:54:01,459 --> 01:54:05,771
Don't cry, baby. Is all right.
Is all right.

1625
01:54:05,939 --> 01:54:10,410
What you heard was lies. Just lies.
The press will be here in a moment.

1626
01:54:10,579 --> 01:54:14,811
I want you here with me
to answer questions.

1627
01:54:16,539 --> 01:54:19,656
He sure busted up that dream of mine.

1628
01:54:26,899 --> 01:54:31,051
We're leaving.
We're leaving here right now.

1629
01:54:31,499 --> 01:54:34,252
My daughter will be here
to answer any and all questions.

1630
01:54:34,419 --> 01:54:36,137
Heavenly! Get in the house!

1631
01:54:36,299 --> 01:54:37,448
Go.

1632
01:54:38,179 --> 01:54:42,252
Papa, I'm never coming
into that house again.

1633
01:54:42,419 --> 01:54:44,091
Wait. Hold it, governor.

1634
01:54:44,259 --> 01:54:46,568
I'll call you back.

1635
01:54:46,739 --> 01:54:48,616
Come back here!

1636
01:54:48,779 --> 01:54:50,417
Come back!

1637
01:54:52,659 --> 01:54:56,857
- Nonnie, she can't leave here. Not now.
- Why?

1638
01:54:57,019 --> 01:55:03,094
- Me. What about me?
- You? You can go straight to hell.

1639
01:55:08,619 --> 01:55:10,610
Subtitles by
SDI Media Group

1640
01:55:10,779 --> 01:55:12,770
[ENGLISH]

